    "data": {
      "text": "MR PELVIS (PROSTATE) WITHOUT & WITH IV CONTRAST\r\n\r\nCLINICAL INDICATION:  Elevated PSA. Most recent PSA 6.22\r\n(030-2019). History of prior negative biopsy (2001).\r\n\r\nCOMPARISON:  None.\r\n\r\nTECHNIQUE:  Informed consent obtained. Multiparametric\r\nmultiplanar, multisequence MRI of the pelvis was performed on a\r\n3-Tesla MRI unit with attention to the prostate gland utilizing\r\nan external surface coil before and after the administration of\r\nintravenous gadolinium-based contrast. Axial TSE T1w,\r\naxial/sagittal/coronal TSE T2w, diffusion-weighted imaging with\r\nADC maps (b-values up to 1500), and dynamic contrast-enhanced\r\nsequences were performed. CAD was utilized with a separate\r\nadvanced post-processing workstation (DynaCAD). No reported\r\ncomplications.\r\n\r\nCONTRAST:  7 mL Gadavist.\r\n\r\nFINDINGS:\r\n\r\nPROSTATE GLAND:\r\n - Size:  Enlarged.\r\n - Dimensions:  4.4 x 5.3 x 6.7 cm (AP x TV x CC).\r\n - Calculated Volume:  81.81 mL.\r\n\r\nCentral Gland: \r\n - Moderate to severe changes of benign prostatic hyperplasia.\r\nProminent median lobe projects into the bladder. No suspicious\r\nfocal central gland abnormality.\r\n\r\nPeripheral zone: \r\n - Atrophic with mildly heterogeneous background T2\r\nhyperintensity. No suspicious focal restricted diffusion,\r\ncircumscribed T2 hypointensity, or focal early hyperenhancement.\r\n\r\nTransition zone:\r\n - Multiple background heterogeneous encapsulated nodules in\r\nkeeping with benign prostatic hyperplasia.\r\n\r\nSeminal vesicles:  \r\n - Within normal limits. Note is made of a prostatic utricle\r\ncyst, benign.\r\n\r\nNeurovascular Bundles:  \r\n - Within normal limits.\r\n\r\nUrinary bladder:  \r\n - Trabeculated hypertrophic wall thickening, most compatible\r\nchronic bladder outlet obstruction.\r\n\r\nLymph nodes:  \r\n - No suspicious pelvic lymphadenopathy.\r\n\r\nBones:  \r\n - No suspicious destructive osseous lesion.\r\n\r\n\r\nOTHER:  \r\n\r\nStatus post right and possibly left inguinal hernia repair.\r\n\r\n\r\n"
    },
