    "data": {
      "text": "\r\nMRI PELVIS W&W/O CONTRAST\r\n\r\nClinical Indication: Prostate cancer.\r\n\r\nTechnique: Multi-parametric prostate MRI using 8.5 cc of Gadavist\r\nintravenous contrast.  \r\n\r\nComparison: MRI dated 11/01/2017.\r\n\r\nResults: \r\n\r\nBiopsy = positive on 02/08/2018\r\n\r\nPSA = 6.18 ng/mL\r\n\r\nPSA density = 0.15 ng/mL/cc\r\n\r\nThe prostate gland measures 3.3 x 4.6 x 4 cm (40 cc) with mild\r\nchanges of BPH within the transitional zone. No focal suspicious\r\nT2 signal within the transitional zone. Two focal areas of\r\nhypointense ADC signal measuring 1.2 cm in the anterolateral\r\nright peripheral zone at the base and 1.7 cm in the\r\nposterolateral right peripheral zone at the mid gland/apex appear\r\nslightly enlarged from prior MRI and demonstrate corresponding\r\nhypointense T2 signal, hyperintense high b-value DWI signal, and\r\ntype III curve kinetic enhancement. The posterolateral right\r\nperipheral zone lesion demonstrates a broad base of contact with\r\nthe capsule suggestive of extraprostatic extension with\r\nencroachment of the right neurovascular bundle. Seminal vesicles\r\nare symmetric. Intact mesorectal fat.\r\n\r\nNo focal bladder wall thickening. No free fluid. No enlarged\r\npelvic lymph nodes.\r\n\r\nImaged bowel and rectum without wall thickening. Small\r\nfat-containing left inguinal hernia.\r\n\r\nNo suspicious bone marrow signal or enhancement.\r\n\r\n"
    },
